The paper deals with the reachability problem for a specific type of hybrid system, namely constant-rate multi-mode systems. This falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses algorithms for solving the reachability problem, which involves computational methods and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper compares the performance of different algorithms, which involves planning and optimization (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
